Thethree marks of existencerefnnoteUnderstanding of these marks helps in the development of detachment:
* [[Anicca]]'' (Sanskrit: ''anitya''): That all things that come to be have an end;
* ''[[Dukkha]]'' (Sanskrit: ''{{IAST|duḥkha}}''): That nothing which comes to be is ultimately satisfying;
* ''[[Anatta|Anattā]]'' (Sanskrit: ''anātman''): That nothing in the realm of experience can really be said to be "I" or "mine".may reflect Upanishadic or other influences. K.R. Norman supposes that these terms were already in use at the Buddha's time, and were familiar to his listeners.sfnNorman199726
